article.headline: Prairie View 73, Jackson St. 59
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Jourdan DeMuynck scored 22 points and Prairie View A&M beat Jackson State 73-59 Monday night. Jules Montgomery had 15 points and Josh Eleby scored 11 for the Panthers (7-11, 2/3 SWAC). Montrael Scott scored 10 points for Prairie View. Dundrecous Nelson led Jackson State (1-14, 0-6) with 24 points, but he was the only Tiger to score in double figures. The Tigers led 32-31 at halftime. Prairie View shot 38 percent for the game while Jackson State was at 34 percent.
